A4.text: Daniel Akaka served as a United States Senator from Hawaii from 1990 to 2013.

A5.text: He was succeeded by fellow Democrat Mazie Hirono.

A6.text: Hirono defeated Lingle with 63% of the vote.

A7.text: She is the first female senator from Hawaii, as well as the first Asian-born immigrant to be elected to the U.S. Senate.
